Path: godot/classes/class_streampeerextension.rst
Summary: Private methods for data handling in StreamPeerExtension with no available documentation

- _get_available_bytes() → int (virtual, required, const): No description available. Returns the number of available bytes in the stream.

- _get_data(r_buffer: uint8_t*, r_bytes: int, r_received: int32_t*) → Error (virtual): No description available. Retrieves data from the stream into a buffer, returning the number of bytes received.

- _get_partial_data(r_buffer: uint8_t*, r_bytes: int, r_received: int32_t*) → Error (virtual): No description available. Retrieves a partial data chunk from the stream into a buffer, returning the number of bytes received.

- _put_data(p_data: const uint8_t*, p_bytes: int, r_sent: int32_t*) → Error (virtual): No description available. Sends data from a buffer to the stream, returning the number of bytes successfully sent.

- _put_partial_data(p_data: const uint8_t*, p_bytes: int, r_sent: int32_t*) → Error (virtual): No description available. Sends a partial data chunk from a buffer to the stream, returning the number of bytes successfully sent.